abstract: In a new Travel column, Sarah Firshein aims to help travelers resolve their thorniest travel disasters. This week, she investigates a flight that got away.
snippet: In a new Travel column, Sarah Firshein aims to help travelers resolve their thorniest travel disasters. This week, she investigates a flight that got away.
lead_paragraph: Sadly, you’re right — you did lose the value of your Icelandair ticket. But despite what you were told, it’s not because you checked in online. You could theoretically check in from Mars and still change your flight afterward. What matters most is your whereabouts — and ticket status — when the plane actually departs.

abstract: Saddling up for the Longines Global Champions Tour in New York.
snippet: Saddling up for the Longines Global Champions Tour in New York.
lead_paragraph: Fun fact about show jumping: While the sport may never shake its elitist reputation, it’s the rare Olympic event where men and women compete against one another. Also true: Admission to last weekend’s Longines Global Champions Tour, which was on Governors Island in New York City and showcased some of the world’s top-ranked jumpers, was free.

abstract: Key officials said they were open-minded about the need for further cuts. Then a flurry of bad economic data rolled in.
snippet: Key officials said they were open-minded about the need for further cuts. Then a flurry of bad economic data rolled in.
lead_paragraph: Top Federal Reserve officials have said they are open-minded about whether additional interest rate cuts will be necessary in 2019, but recent economic data are putting that equanimity to the test.

abstract: The plan marks the first major expansion of schools since Mayor Bill de Blasio took office nearly six years ago.
snippet: The plan marks the first major expansion of schools since Mayor Bill de Blasio took office nearly six years ago.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio has decided to use about $16 million in private funding from an education organization backed by Laurene Powell Jobs, the widow of Steve Jobs, and from Robin Hood, a philanthropic powerhouse favored by Wall Street executives, to help open a host of new and restructured public schools in New York City.

snippet: The pace may allow the electric-car maker to fulfill its forecast for the year. But analysts are skeptical that sales are enough to yield a profit.
lead_paragraph: Tesla reported record quarterly deliveries on Wednesday, putting the electric-car maker within reach of its goal for the year. But analysts remain skeptical that the company will show a profit for the period.
